President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate individuals to key positions in his Administration. Justin E. Herdman is nominated to serve as United States Attorney for the District of Columbia. He currently serves as the United States Attorney for the Northern District of Ohio and is a member of the Attorney General's Advisory Committee of United States Attorneys. Prior to his role as US Attorney, Herdman was a partner at Jones Day and served as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Northern District of Ohio.

Chris Koos is nominated to be a Director of the Amtrak Board of Directors. He is currently the Mayor of Normal, Illinois and has held the position since 2003. Koos is also involved in various transportation and business associations in his community.

Sarah E. Feinberg is nominated to be a Director of the Amtrak Board of Directors. She currently serves as the Interim President of New York City Transit and previously served as Administrator of the Federal Railroad Administration. Feinberg has experience in policy communications and business strategy, having worked at Facebook and Bloomberg L.P. She is the founder of Feinberg Strategies, LLC.